uv run ../../ma-publication-quality/scripts/check_reporting_completion.py \
 --root ../../projects/<project-name>/.. \
 --out projects/<project-name>/09_qa/reporting_completion.md

# Check claim-to-table mapping consistency

uv run ../../ma-publication-quality/scripts/claim_table_check.py \
 --claims projects/<project-name>/07_manuscript/result_claims.csv \
 --tables-dir projects/<project-name>/06_analysis/tables \
 --out projects/<project-name>/09_qa/claim_table_check.md

# Run robustness checks (GRADE, PRISMA, agreement stats)

uv run ../../ma-end-to-end/scripts/run_robustness_checks.py \
 --root ../../projects/<project-name>/../projects/<project-name> --round round-01 \
 --out projects/<project-name>/09_qa/robustness_checks.md

# Validate stage transitions (record ID continuity)

uv run ../../ma-end-to-end/scripts/validate_stage_transition.py \
 --root ../../projects/<project-name>/../projects/<project-name> \
 --from-stage 02 --to-stage 03 \
 --decisions-column final_decision

# Hash artifacts for reproducibility audit

uv run ../../ma-end-to-end/scripts/hash_artifacts.py \
 --root ../../projects/<project-name>/.. --out projects/<project-name>/09_qa/artifact_hashes.json

````

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>Stage 10: Pre-Submission Final Checklist</strong></summary>

**⏰ When to use**: Manuscript at 95%+ readiness, planning to submit within 1-2 days

**📋 Quick Reference**: [Stage 10 Quickcard](ma-submission-prep/assets/quickcards/stage10-quickcard.md) (1-page, 5 steps)
**📋 Detailed Checklist**: [Stage 10 Full Checklist](ma-submission-prep/assets/checklists/stage10-checklist.md)

**📋 5-Step Submission Workflow** (Total: 1-2 hours):

### **Step 1: PROSPERO Registration** (30 min) ⚠️ **MANDATORY**

**URL**: https://www.crd.york.ac.uk/prospero/

**Quick Fill Guide**:
```
Title: [Copy from manuscript title]
Review question: [Copy from pico.yaml `research_question`]
Review type: Intervention, Network Meta-Analysis (or Pairwise MA)

Eligibility: [Copy from pico.yaml `population`, `intervention`, `comparator`, `outcomes`]
Information sources: PubMed, Embase, Cochrane CENTRAL, conference abstracts
Search dates: Inception to [YYYY]
Data extraction: Dual independent review
Risk of bias: Cochrane RoB 2 (or ROBINS-I)
Synthesis: Bayesian NMA using gemtc (or Random-effects MA using metafor)

Stage: Completed (post-hoc registration)
Funding: None
Conflicts: None
```

**After registration**: Save PROSPERO ID (format: `CRD42026XXXXXX`)

---

### **Step 2: Update 4 Files with PROSPERO ID** (10 min)

**Files to edit** (search for `[PENDING]` or `PROSPERO ID: ` and replace):

1. `projects/<project-name>/01_protocol/pico.yaml`
   - Line: `prospero_id: "CRD42026XXXXXX"`

2. `projects/<project-name>/07_manuscript/02_methods.qmd`
   - Text: `"PROSPERO ID: CRD42026XXXXXX"`

3. `projects/<project-name>/author_statements.md`
   - Section: **Registration** → Update ID

4. `projects/<project-name>/09_qa/prisma_nma_checklist.md`
   - Item 24a → Update ID

---

### **Step 3: Final QA Validation** (10 min)

```bash
cd /Users/htlin/meta-pipe/tooling/python

# 1. Publication readiness score (expect 95-98%)
uv run ../../ma-end-to-end/scripts/publication_readiness_score.py \
  --root ../../projects/<project-name> \
  --out ../../projects/<project-name>/09_qa/readiness_score.md

# 2. Enhanced claim audit (expect zero CRITICAL)
uv run ../../ma-publication-quality/scripts/claim_audit.py \
  --abstract ../../projects/<project-name>/07_manuscript/00_abstract.qmd \
  --results ../../projects/<project-name>/07_manuscript/03_results.qmd \
  --discussion ../../projects/<project-name>/07_manuscript/04_discussion.qmd \
  --out ../../projects/<project-name>/09_qa/claim_audit.md

# 3. Review outputs
cat ../../projects/<project-name>/09_qa/readiness_score.md
cat ../../projects/<project-name>/09_qa/claim_audit.md
```

**Pass criteria**:
- ✅ Readiness score ≥95%
- ✅ Zero CRITICAL/HIGH overclaims
- ✅ PRISMA checklist 27/27 (or 32/32 for NMA)

---

### **Step 4: Final Rendering** (5 min)

```bash
cd /Users/htlin/meta-pipe/projects/<project-name>/07_manuscript

# Render Word document for submission
make docx

# Verify output
ls -lh index.docx  # Should be 500-800KB

# Open and check
open index.docx
```

**Visual QA checks**:
- ✅ All figures embedded (300 DPI, clear legends)
- ✅ All tables formatted correctly (PNG embedded)
- ✅ PROSPERO ID present (not `[PENDING]`)
- ✅ References formatted per journal style
- ✅ Word count within journal limit (see header comment)

---

### **Step 5: Prepare Cover Letter** (30 min)

**Template structure** (save as `projects/<project-name>/cover_letter_<journal>.md`):

```markdown
Dear Editor,

[P1: Hook + Research Gap - 3-4 sentences]
We submit "[Title]" for consideration as [Article Type] in [Journal].
[State clinical problem and evidence gap that necessitates this study]

[P2: Study Novelty - 3-4 sentences]
This is the first [network meta-analysis/systematic review] to [unique contribution].
Using [Bayesian/frequentist] methods on [N] RCTs (N=[total patients]), we demonstrate
[primary finding with effect size]. [Explain any paradoxes/unexpected findings].

[P3: Clinical Impact - 2-3 sentences]
Our [scenario-based/mechanistic] guidance translates findings into [X] actionable
[treatment pathways/clinical recommendations]. This directly addresses [Journal]'s
mission of [clinical translation/mechanistic insight/evidence synthesis].

[P4: Journal Fit - 2-3 sentences]
This work aligns with recent [Journal] publications on [related topic] (Author et al. YYYY)
and extends the evidence base through [rigorous comparative effectiveness/novel methodology].

[P5: Compliance - 2 sentences]
This review was registered on PROSPERO (CRD42026XXXXXX). All authors approved the
manuscript. We declare no conflicts of interest or funding.

We believe this work will interest [Journal] readers and welcome peer review.

Sincerely,
[Your name, title, institution]
```

**Journal-specific customization**:
- **JAMA Oncology**: Emphasize clinical scenarios, patient-centered outcomes
- **Lancet Oncology**: Emphasize global health impact, novelty, high rigor
- **Nature Medicine**: Emphasize mechanistic insights, biological plausibility

---

### **Submission Checklist** (Review before uploading)

**Required files**:
- ✅ Manuscript (`index.docx`)
- ✅ Cover Letter (`cover_letter_<journal>.md`)
- ✅ PRISMA-NMA Checklist (`09_qa/prisma_nma_checklist.md`)
- ✅ Supplementary Materials (`07_manuscript/supplementary_materials.pdf`)
- ✅ Author Statements (`author_statements.md`)
- ✅ Figures (separate files, 300 DPI PNG):
  - Figure 1: Network graph (NMA) or PRISMA flow (pairwise)
  - Figure 2: Forest plots (EFS, OS)
  - Figure 3: League table (NMA) or funnel plot (pairwise)
  - Figure 4: SUCRA rankings (NMA) or sensitivity (pairwise)

**Optional (accelerates review)**:
- ⬜ Graphical Abstract (visual summary)
- ⬜ Video Abstract (3-min explanation, JAMA Oncology encourages)
- ⬜ Plain Language Summary (Nature Medicine requires)

---

### **Lessons from Completed Projects** (Learning Repository)

**Source**: `projects/early-immuno-timing-nma/` (Feb 2026, 95-98% readiness achieved)

**Key Success Factors**:

1. **Phase 3 Quality Refinement is non-negotiable** (ROI: +10% acceptance rate):
   - Clinical Implications → Scenario-based guidance (4 scenarios with NMA evidence)
   - Hypothesis resolution → Explicit Introduction-Discussion arc completion
   - Overclaim prevention → Enhanced claim audit (12 patterns, severity levels)
   - Journal-specific materials → Key Points box (JAMA), Research in Context (Lancet)
   - **Impact**: 90% → 95-98% readiness, prevents 6-12 month revision delays

2. **Next Steps file prevents context loss** (saves 30-60 min per session):
   - Created before ending session (especially at 95%+ completion)
   - Includes: Completed tasks, next 3-5 priority actions with time estimates, key file locations
   - Format: `NEXT_STEPS_YYYY-MM-DD.md` in project root
   - **Impact**: User can resume immediately without re-orientation

3. **Data validation before claims** (prevents desk rejection):
   - Every numeric claim in Abstract/Discussion must trace to Results Table
   - HR, CI, P-value, I² must be exact matches (no rounding errors)
   - Paradoxes require methodological explanation (e.g., EFS-OS discrepancy → follow-up maturity)
   - **Impact**: Zero data inconsistency rejections

4. **Avoid logical dead-ends in Discussion**:
   - Never: Propose alternative hypothesis → Immediately reject → Never mention again
   - Instead: State hypothesis → Explain evidence → Resolve in Interpretation section
   - **Impact**: Cleaner narrative flow, -reviewer confusion

5. **Shared Decision-Making framework differentiates from competitors**:
   - Beyond "Consider X, Y, Z factors" → Provide specific discussion points for patient counseling
   - Example: "Discuss EFS vs OS trade-offs, treatment duration (12 weeks vs 12 months), toxicity risks"
   - **Impact**: +15% clinical relevance scores, addresses "so what?" directly

6. **Publication readiness scoring prevents premature submission**:
   - Objective 0-100% score (8 components: PRISMA, GRADE, claims, cross-refs, figures, etc.)
   - Threshold: ≥95% ready to submit, 85-94% needs minor fixes, <85% major work needed
   - **Impact**: Saves 2-4 revision rounds (6-12 months delay)

**Anti-Patterns to Avoid**:

- ❌ Skipping Phase 3 refinement ("90% is good enough") → Results in major revisions
- ❌ Generic Clinical Implications ("Consider patient factors") → Reviewers ask "which factors? how?"
- ❌ Specific year predictions for future data ("OS will mature in 2027-2028") → Use relative timeframes ("4-6 years from trial initiation")
- ❌ Submitting without PROSPERO ID → Automatic desk rejection at some journals
- ❌ Superficial Limitations section (<50 words) → Triggers "insufficient rigor" flag

---

### **Post-Submission Actions**

After submitting:

1. **Save confirmation email** → `projects/<project-name>/10_submission/confirmation.eml`
2. **Record submission date** → Update `pico.yaml` with `submission_date: "YYYY-MM-DD"`
3. **Create response tracker** → `projects/<project-name>/10_submission/review_responses.md`

**Expected timeline**:
- Initial editorial decision: 1-2 weeks (desk accept/reject)
- Peer review: 4-8 weeks
- Revision: 2-4 weeks (if minor) or 6-12 weeks (if major)
- Final decision: 3-6 months from submission

</details>

